  "prompt": "Where can you find replays of NBA games?",
  "response": "You can find replays of NBA games on several platforms:\n\n1. **NBA League Pass**: This is the official service provided by the NBA, where subscribers can watch live games and replays. It offers a comprehensive archive of past games.\n\n2. **ESPN**: The ESPN app and website often have highlights and sometimes full-game replays available.\n\n3. **TNT**: The network often has replays of games, especially those broadcast on their channel. You can check the TNT app or website for availability.\n\n4. **YouTube**: While full games might not always be available due to broadcasting restrictions, you can find extended highlights and certain games from past seasons uploaded unofficially by users.\n\n5. **Local and Regional Sports Networks**: RSNs that have broadcast rights to certain teams often provide replays of games either directly on their websites/apps or through their cable service.\n\n6. **Streaming Services**: Services like Hulu Live, YouTube TV, and Sling TV which offer live TV may also have partnerships with channels that broadcast NBA games and could provide on-demand replays.\n\nRemember to check for any subscription requirements or geo-restrictions that may apply.",
